# Base URL of the Graceward API the app calls for AI reflection.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ vars are inlined into the client at build time.
#
# iOS Simulator: the simulator shares the Mac's network, so localhost works:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# Physical iPhone (Expo Go / dev build): use your Mac's LAN IP instead of
# localhost (find it with `ipconfig getifaddr en0`), and run the API with
# HOST=0.0.0.0 so it accepts LAN connections. Phone and Mac must share Wi-Fi:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.50:3000
#
# Production / TestFlight builds: point at the deployed HTTPS API. The API must
# be deployed first (see docs/14_DEPLOYMENT.md) or AI reflection will fail with
# a calm "not available" error. For EAS builds this is set per-profile in
# eas.json rather than from this file:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.graceward.app
#
# NOTE: EXPO_PUBLIC_ vars ship inside the app bundle. Only put the public API
# base URL here — never the OpenAI key or any server-side secret.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
